## 🧠 Problem Statement
[Q3](https://github.com/aarushijain16/SQL-Business-Analytics-Case-Study/blob/main/Queries/Q3.sql). Identify the top 3 customers based on total revenue generated.

## 🎯 Objective
To identify high-value customers who contribute the most to overall revenue, enabling targeted retention and engagement strategies.

## 🛠️ Approach
- Aggregated total revenue at the customer level using SUM()
- Joined customers, orders, and order_items tables to capture complete transaction data
- Used a Common Table Expression (CTE) to structure intermediate results
- Applied ROW_NUMBER() to rank customers based on revenue in descending order
- Filtered the top 3 customers using rank

## ⚙️ Why This Function?
ROW_NUMBER() is used to assign a unique rank to each customer based on revenue contribution.  
It is preferred over RANK() or DENSE_RANK() because it ensures exactly 3 customers are selected, even when multiple customers have the same revenue.  
Additionally, ordering by customer_id ensures deterministic ranking in case of ties.

## 💡 Business Insight
This analysis helps businesses:
- Identify high-value customers for retention and personalized engagement  
- Allocate resources toward customers with the highest revenue impact  
- Recognize low-value customers and design strategies to improve their contribution  
